SOLD

I am changing collecting direction and am offering this really nice British Enfield No.4 MK 1* Long Branch 1942.

The rifle is all matching serial number on the Rifle, Bolt and Magazine
There is a small import mark on the very end of the barrel on the right side, can be easily missed if you didn't
know where to look for it.

I have fired 100 rounds down the tube without any problems. 

1. The rifle pass's the Field Gauge test
2. Also pass's the Bore Erosion Gauge test
(using British Military Throat Erosion gauge 4139 SA & MG)
3. Rifle also pass's the Muzzle Bullet test

The Bolt - shows the LB symbol
The Bolt Head - is a size "O" and has the LB symbol & the C-broad arrow The Cocking Piece of the bolt - has the LB symbol 


Stock is really nice with normal wear marks that would commonly be found
on rifles of this age. Rifle has the Early Grooved Rear Hand Guard (see pictures)

title: For Sale:  Colt Model 1862 Police
postcontent: This is one of those hard to find first year production Colt Model 1862 Police Revolvers in excellent condition. According to Flayderman’s, the Model 1862 is considered by many collectors as the ultimate in streamlined design by Colt’s factory during the percussion period. Serial number 2632 this gun was manufactured in 1861. 36 Cal.5 shot. This one has a 4 ½” round barrel with the COL. SAML COLT NEW YORK USA AMERICA barrel address. COLTS/PATENT is stamped on the left side of the frame and PAT SEPT 10TH 1850 is stamped within one of the cylinder flutes. Serial number matches the cylinder, frame, trigger guard, arbor, back strap and wedge. Nipples are in good condition. There is evidence of 4 remaining safety pins. The gun retains a great deal of color. The trigger and wedge have a high percentage of blue while the bottom four screws and loading lever screws retain their fire blue finish. The frame has a high percentage of case coloring remaining. The back strap has a generous amount of tarnished silver at the butt and frame. The cylinder is plum brown with bluing in the cylinder stops. The barrel has about 50% of its blue. The bore has fine lands and grooves and is still shiny. The one piece varnished walnut grips are in excellent condition and retain at least 95% of the original varnish. Action is crisp and tight. It would be hard to find one better.  Unfortunately, no information exists at the Colt Archives to letter any Colt Model 1862.  This is an antique firearm that can be shipped directly to your door. The purchase price includes FREE shipping and a Custom Made Oak and Glass Display case shown in the photo.  MORE Old Colts and info at www.oldcolts.com

This is a Polish 9mm Semi-Automatic Pistol designed to fire the 9x18 Makarov cartridge. The pistol was developed in the late 1950s at the Institute for Artillery Research(Zaklad Broni Strzeleckiej Centralnego Badawczego Poligonu Artyleryjskiego). This is a crate of Yugoslavian BRASS case 7.62x39 ammunition.  It utilizes the M67 bullet for greater wounding effect, and is loaded hotter than most other standard ammunition in addition to being considerably more accurate. Easier on your extractor than most steel cased ammo.  It comes in a wooden case, and hermetically sealed in a zinc tin.  The ammunition is packed in boxes on SKS chargers, so you get 112 of those along with the ammo. This stuff was manufactured by the SAME factory that is currently producing PRVI Partizan ammunition, so trust me, it's quality.Oh, and it's a lot of fun to open these guys up and smell the history.



The ammo in this configuration has been sold out for some time. I've run through a case before and it's GOOD stuff.  I'm just selling it because of a financial issue. Would prefer cash or bank money order.

postcontent:

Has been modified with Wolff springs to reduce recoil, double action pull and mag release force. Recoil and double action pull are the two main complaints about this gun. The small size and single stack mag makes this a very nice gun for concealed carry. Fits easily in a pocket and there are various holsters available.

Face to face with Ohio resident over 21 only.
